commit_message:
Make HTTP client aware of no_proxy variable

Fix the problem of ceilometer client ignoring the host list in
no_proxy environment variable. Now proxy url is only used when
the Host of target URL is not in the no_proxy host list.

Closes-Bug: #1310805
Change-Id: I0b841291f1e8b9d9c7f431efd7d8f95d37df72b6

commit_message:
Make sure instance_type_id index exist when db sync

When upgrade database from folsom to grizzly, then to havana. 184 -> 185 will
raise a exception. The reason is table 'instance_type_projects' lost a index
'instance_type_id' after running 174_add_instance_type_access_uc.

The patch make sure the index 'instance_type_id' is existed after adding UC.

Change-Id: Ib15dc87aa8af3f0f8070693283da77ee66fd42c8
Closes-Bug: #1239484

commit_message:
Fixes Hyper-V boot from volume live migration

Live migration fails on Hyper-V when boot from volume is used with
CoW, as the target host tries to cache the root disk image in
pre_live_migration, but in this case the image_ref is empty.

This patch adds a check to handle the empty image_ref case.

Change-Id: I60cb60ccaeb0cb8c536906d897249e31ae396923
Closes-Bug: #1362075

'}, {'created': '2014-09-02 11:46:42.000000000', 'message': 'Uniquify horizon messages returned in a single response

A network operation can fail because of different
reasons - yet in many places just one error message
is provided. Combined with too broad exception clause,
and incorrect assumptions on the reasons of failure
(e.g. Neutron service being unavailable causes all
other sorts of errors like inability to Allocate IP
or Associate it) lead to multiple errors when just one
would suffice. The fix aims to provide sensible error
messages in case the network service is down. This includes
returning only unique messages in a single response.

Closes-Bug: #1301374
Change-Id: Id6c620ca51f7703f35c0c172e39fdf237fa42278

commit_message:
Uniquify horizon messages returned in a single response

A network operation can fail because of different
reasons - yet in many places just one error message
is provided. Combined with too broad exception clause,
and incorrect assumptions on the reasons of failure
(e.g. Neutron service being unavailable causes all
other sorts of errors like inability to Allocate IP
or Associate it) this leads to multiple errors when just one
would suffice. The fix aims to provide sensible error
messages in case the network service is down. This includes
returning only unique messages in a single response.

Partial-Bug: #1301374
Change-Id: Id6c620ca51f7703f35c0c172e39fdf237fa42278
Co-Authored-By: Timur Sufiev <tsufiev@mirantis.com>

commit_message:
Modified docs to update DevStack's config filename

As reported in the bug, the documentation needs to be updated with
new config file DevStack uses. This patch simply updates information
in "Installing and Running the Development Version" page.

Change-Id: I5ee8f528be44b4fe801b38c748fff7314980a93e
Closes-Bug: #1370476

[{'created': '2014-07-10 05:56:08.000000000', 'message': "CLI image-update gives a wrong help on '--tags' param

The help message tells end user image-update interface accepts 'tags'
param and could be used to update tag of image [0], but actually it
could trigger an 400 exception [1] due to wrong PATCH calls, and the
correct way is to use image-tag-update interface [2] as designed.

[0] glance image-update <IMG_ID> --tags <TAG_VALUE>

[1] 400 Bad Request
    Invalid JSON pointer for this resource: '/tags/0'
        (HTTP 400)

[2] glance image-tag-update <IMG_ID> <TAG_VALUE>

Change-Id: Iaa8041779510192dc08f7b898b8a1beda29a6398
Signed-off-by: Zhi Yan Liu <zhiyanl@cn.ibm.com>"}]
commit_message:
CLI image-update gives a wrong help on '--tags' param

The help message tells end user image-update interface accepts 'tags'
param and could be used to update tag of image [0], but actually it
could trigger an 400 exception [1] due to wrong PATCH calls, and the
correct way is to use image-tag-update interface [2] as designed.

[0] glance image-update <IMG_ID> --tags <TAG_VALUE>

[1] 400 Bad Request
    Invalid JSON pointer for this resource: '/tags/0'
        (HTTP 400)

[2] glance image-tag-update <IMG_ID> <TAG_VALUE>

Change-Id: Iaa8041779510192dc08f7b898b8a1beda29a6398
Signed-off-by: Zhi Yan Liu <zhiyanl@cn.ibm.com>

commit_message:
Remove keystone-specs from the projects.txt

Keystone-specs is the only specs repository that was in this list
and it appears we aren't doing the same global-requirements gating
on the -specs repos.

This removes the keystone-specs repo until we determine if we want
to do global-requirements gating on -specs repos.

Change-Id: Ia1ca5e158b8c7080637fea1bff2dc252c6cc7ce1

commit_message:
Remove kvm as a hypervisor_type argument

QEMU is used whether specifying either qemu or kvm as an argument to
hypervisor_type. Therefore, remove kvm as a supported argument.

Change-Id: I89f2b907fa868e50c2b65c2bf4a8e414242dd9fc
Closes-bug: #1195361

[{'created': '2014-09-13 07:30:07.000000000', 'message': "Stop using intersphinx

Remove intersphinx from the docs build as it triggers network calls that
occasionally fail, and we don't really use intersphinx (links other
sphinx documents out on the internet)

This also removes the requirement for internet access during docs build.

This can cause docs jobs to fail if the project errors out on
warnings.

Change-Id: I71e941e2a639641a662a163c682eb86d51de42fb
Related-Bug: #1368910
"}]
commit_message:
Stop using intersphinx

Remove intersphinx from the docs build as it triggers network calls that
occasionally fail, and we don't really use intersphinx (links other
sphinx documents out on the internet)

This also removes the requirement for internet access during docs build.

This can cause docs jobs to fail if the project errors out on
warnings.

Change-Id: I71e941e2a639641a662a163c682eb86d51de42fb
Related-Bug: #1368910

commit_message:
Standardize the async result subclasses

Move away from these subclasses exposing there properties
as publicly viewable and have them only expose the base
class functions as things that are publicly useable.

This also adjusts how the zookeeper async result had a usage
of camelcasing that didn't seem to fit in the other naming
conventions that tooz uses.

Change-Id: Iaa1dd3bb7b359b2dab14a8aeeab9f2e3e9cd8d29

commit_message:
Add oslo_release.sh script

Add an oslo_release.sh script to help with alpha and final releases of
Oslo libraries. It makes use of an utility to rename Launchpad
milestones.

Change-Id: Ib87a22834eb79a12b46023b030cfef495d14540f

commit_message:
Retitle list of libraries

The PyCADF library is no part of the Oslo "Common Libraries" program.
Rather than reogranizing the documentation set around our governance,
retitle the libraries list more generically.

Change-Id: I07eb43a773256557e26b3478b411605c36f567c3

[{'created': '2014-09-19 00:22:13.000000000', 'message': '[DOC] Removed note about SAHARA_USE_NEUTRON in sahara-dashboard

Sahara-dashboard was merged to horizon. Horizon detects neutron by
itself and no additional settings are needed. Deleted the whole
section.

Change-Id: Id6bca92f924d271eed5a78b912b4014e25bb1ea8
'}]
commit_message:
[DOC] Removed note about SAHARA_USE_NEUTRON in sahara-dashboard

Sahara-dashboard was merged to horizon. Horizon detects neutron by
itself and no additional settings are needed. Deleted the whole
section.

Change-Id: Id6bca92f924d271eed5a78b912b4014e25bb1ea8

commit_message:
update incorrect keystone.conf file path and missing space.

the file path Keystone conf file is located under /etc/keystone/keystone.conf instead of /etc/keystone.conf

Under Section Invalid login attempts, the sentence has a missing space before Detection:

If prevention is not an option, detection can be used to mitigate damage.Detection involves frequent

It is changed to:

If prevention is not an option, detection can be used to mitigate damage. Detection involves frequent

Change-Id: I82bc0144f9a9047f74dbbabf6dc12242f255a35c
Closes-Bug: #1368422

commit_message:
Adm policy can't use other tenants unshared rules

If the firewall rules are not shared and if they belong to different
tenants, then admin should not be able to create a policy using
these rules and he should not be able to insert such rules into
policies. An exception should be raised in such case. Added new
‚ÄúFirewallRuleConflict‚Äù exception to handle such conditions.

Change-Id: Iac54ac8dfd96cce93ce938a23c9c976d09ab57d3
Closes-bug: 1327057

commit_message:
Install the psmisc package in the keepalived element

The chk_haproxy track script uses killall, which isn't installed on the
fedora cloud image.

Change-Id: Ia62aa1b40df75ece5ed370fd2dfdee56c2c8ee28

commit_message:
Update doc for qos_policy_group NetApp extra spec

Bug 1288283 updated the function behind the qos_policy_group extra spec,
but the docs were never updated to reflect the change in behavior from
being a capability advertised to the scheduler to being a directive that
needed to be executed post provisioning.

Cherry-picked from master:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/122302/

In the above commit (https://review.openstack.org/#/c/122302/), I
didn't follow the doc guidelines and used the term Cinder. This fixes
this snafoo.

Cherry-picked from master:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/122487/

Change-Id: I226c58c112e8485951834978b4fb971edaad5d81
(cherry picked from commit f6357f2fca0a1bcb526af80a3e52e6adf336b1d7)

We have two imports with #noqa: django.conf.urls.patterns and
django.conf.urls.url however using them is a standard way of creating
any urls.py module. So there are over 150 imports in Horizon code

commit_message:
Remove #noqa from two common imports and add them to import_exceptions

We have two imports with #noqa: django.conf.urls.patterns and
django.conf.urls.url however using them is a standard way of creating
any urls.py module. So there are over 150 imports in Horizon code
where #noqa could be replaced with two lines in list of import_exceptions.

Change-Id: I81c3290e0dc958b5037dd6a87e44df18adfbe751

And there we go :)

By the way, there are ways in git that you could restore a file like .gitignore if you accidentally modify or delete it.  Probably the simplest would be to check it out from the master branch:

    [klmitch@einstein python-novaclient]$ git checkout -b throw-away
    Switched to a new branch 'throw-away'
    [klmitch@einstein python-novaclient]$ rm .gitignore
    [klmitch@einstein python-novaclient]$ git checkout master .gitignore
    [klmitch@einstein python-novaclient]$ git status
    On branch throw-away
    nothing to commit, working directory clean
    [klmitch@einstein python-novaclient]$ echo "foobar" >> .gitignore
    [klmitch@einstein python-novaclient]$ git checkout master .gitignore
    [klmitch@einstein python-novaclient]$ git status
    On branch throw-away
    nothing to commit, working directory clean

Sorry to not have suggested this tool earlier ;)'}, {'account_id': 1849, 'date': '2014-09-17 21:16:50.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 8: Code-Review+2 Workflow+1

commit_message:
Corrects typos "coearse," "proejct," and "unecrypts"

Misspelling of "coerce" found in the docstring body
of method _boot from class ServerManager. Misspellings
of "project" and "unencrypts" found in docstrings
of client.py and crypto.py.

Change-Id: I052c321f3ad5e13aa57a559e2f28ec5eec32a9b4

Workers that don't exit can also trigger a timeout, and we want our

commit_message:
tests: kill worker pids as well on timeouts

Workers that don't exit can also trigger a timeout, and we want our
test environment to be super robust - kill them aggressively too.

Also raise the timeout error so that we don't mask this when it
happens.

Change-Id: Iee606720f98e9a5e8a11f162eb885c0a00a2345e
Partial-Bug: #1357578

commit_message:
Set the default number of workers when running under eventlet

Keystone now defaults to n-cpu as the number of workers under eventlet with
a minimum number of workers when auto-calculating the number of 2.

This behavior can be overridded by changing the `admin_workers` and
`public_workers` configuration values in the Keystone config file.

Change-Id: I482cfef7ee14e995c6fb206bcef412957c54f491
Closes-Bug: #1371154

commit_message:
Add UTF-8 multibyte input validation to createImage server action

Adds extra input validation to the createImage server action
to ensure that invalid multibyte UTF-8 characters are not
in the image name.

Change-Id: I1bbfcfa8e3d379596a9dc4b415322099d4d6819d
Closes-Bug: 1006725

commit_message:
add '--insecure' to keystone command in register

When keystone service need cafile verification, can not
do registration work, we can use insecure mode to do all
registration work only in OpenStack installation process.

Change-Id: I246700aace69b192716982f2985856381cfee029
Closes-Bug: #1369241

commit_message:
Remove PYTHONHASHSEED=0 from tox.ini

We've ironed out remaining issues that crop up when running
with a random seed. This updates tox.ini to revert to the default
behavior of running with PYTHONHASHSEED=random.  The pep8 check
continues to run with PYTHONHASHSEED=0 to workaround oslo issues
around config value ordering in the check_uptodate.sh test.

Change-Id: Ifa0dba8c3970fc676d374f33c129ef0f9d526c94

commit_message:
Ensure 'address' in add_interface

The function _add_interface doesn't check whether the param "address" is
in request body. We should check it and catch KeyError.

Change-Id: Ia15b905e93033b8f5eee03fc2bffdd79dbd31045
Closes-Bug: #1254999

commit_message:
Setup subunit-trace as an entry point

This commit moves subunit-trace into the newly created cmd dir and
adds a pbr entry point to run it as a binary. This will enable using
subunit-trace just by installing tempest-lib.

Change-Id: I3ae379edca3e776e90a18d53393c4c1424d291f7

commit_message:
Safer check for enabled in trusts

For some LDAP backends, the enable attribute is not
directly set.  Since we have a wrapper function in identity/core,
we can use that instead.

Adds tests that disabling trustor or trustee prevents
trust execution.

Closes-Bug: 1367952

Change-Id: I6d3c26e0e6e6c0d27ea7b910340fae5792eaceda

I'd actually be in favor of a stack-update-cancel command separate from stack-update because the --cancel behaves as a different command. It takes none of the same args/options (except stack ID) as update. 

It also requires nesting all but 4 of the existing lines in the update command, which is a signal to me that it's different enough to be its own command.

commit_message:
container.merge_items bug

When replicated container entries get round-tripped through json, they wind up
with unicode objects for names.  This causes equality checks to fail against
container entries, and you can wind up with duplicate records.  My bad.

Change-Id: I3aee2ad8dbd3a617efe37e887cfb902a3e4a1646

commit_message:
Add the processutils from oslo-incubator.

This is a module specific add rather than a full sync. The processutils
module will be used to determine the default number of workers for keystone
running under eventlet.

Processutils sync'd from oslo commit hash 6a60f84258

Change-Id: I6cbca7d54ca97cce962d3cc1131388840ddf9a7c
Related-Bug: #1371154

commit_message:
Update keystone.conf permission

To avoid other users to access scecret in keystone.conf, set the
file permission to 640 instead of 644

Fix bug 1369446
Change-Id: I26af2ae803de9ba909d3356c27a33563fba68af3

So, I agree that nova should not be returning 403 with a Retry-After header.  That said, the rest of this patch makes sense.  Perhaps what's needed is a little bit of error class introspection: if the corresponding error class takes a retry_after parameter (or descends from RetryAfterException), then (and only then) do you consume the Retry-After header."}, {'account_id': 679, 'date': '2014-09-16 15:54:38.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

@Michal: We prefer to keep discussion about a review in the review itself, rather than discussing it via private email.  That helps keep all reviewers in the loop and avoids having everyone asking the same questions over and over :)  Anyway, to try to answer your question about what I meant by my last comment:

Chris Yeoh is suggesting that the actual error is in nova.  I am agreeing and disagreeing‚ÄîI'm saying that yes, nova clearly has an error that needs fixing, but so does python-novaclient‚Ä¶and your proposed solution does help.  I then make a suggestion about what could be a better solution to the problem, and I suspect that's what you're trying to understand.

So, the exceptions in exceptions.py are instantiated by the function from_response().  In from_response(), if 'retry-after' exists in the response headers, then we unconditionally attempt to pass it to the exception itself as a keyword argument retry_after, whether or not the exception takes such a keyword argument.  This leads to the bug you're trying to fix.

The suggestion I'm making is to add an extra clause to this test for the Retry-After header, that tests whether the exception descends from RetryAfterException, and will only pass the keyword argument if it does.  To do this, the "cls = _code_map.get(response.status_code, ClientException)" must be moved to earlier in the function (probably be made the first line of the function).  Then, the 'if' in question becomes:

    if (isinstance(cls, RetryAfterException) and
            'retry-after' in response.headers):
        kwargs['retry_after'] = response.headers.get('retry-after')

This accomplishes the desirable quality of making novaclient more liberal about what it will accept, regardless of the quite legitimate bug that exists in nova.

Does that help?'}, {'account_id': 11600, 'date': '2014-09-17 10:55:27.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 5.'}, {'account_id': 11600, 'date': '2014-09-17 10:56:47.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 6.'}, {'account_id': 11600, 'date': '2014-09-17 10:57:21.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 6:

commit_message:
Add retry_after only to exceptions supporting it

Having retry_after in HTTP response header for 403 status code caused
client to fail with TypeError exception about unexpected keyword
argument. This is related to bug in nova-api. To prevent this kind of
client problems in the future patch adds check to from_response
function to pass retry-after header only to classes that inherit
from RetryAfterException and regression unit tests.

Change-Id: I6bfc8b33eb591d30b3c647397b11100094718e13
Closes-Bug: 1365251

In Debian, we are going to release Jessie with Django 1.7,
which has just been released. Therefore, compatibility is

This patch, which the Debian package already carries, fixes
2 small compatibility issues with Django 1.7. It is safe to

'}]
commit_message:
Fix Django 1.7 compat

In Debian, we are going to release Jessie with Django 1.7,
which has just been released. Therefore, compatibility is
important for us.

This patch, which the Debian package already carries, fixes
2 small compatibility issues with Django 1.7. It is safe to
use openstack_auth with these patches and a lower version of
Django, which makes it safe to apply this patch.

Change-Id: I564cde889c56e12fc0fc1347537e66b576605a0d

commit_message:
Dismiss flavor detail pop-over on users next click

In the Instances table under Projects, when we click the flavor
link under Size column, a flavor details pop-over shows up.
Currently we cannot dismiss this pop-over unless user clicks the
flavor link again.

This patch is intended to fix this issue by dismissing the pop-over
on the user's next click.

Change-Id: I46e4d368ef174f04f245be8eef8b3b244c5d1201
Closes-Bug: #1370133

commit_message:
Style network address for subnet as required field

It does this by adding the required class to the network address field when the
checkbox is enabled.

I have also made the checkbox behave like a switchable select so when the create
subnet checkbox is checked all fields are visible. There are hidden when create
subnet is unselected.

Change-Id: Id45d5ce2a1bb55e4bcaa33df065ca2b1ccee3c7e
Closes-bug: 1367858

Add -c support to devtest_overcloud.sh.

This is similar to the support in devtest_seed.sh. USE_CACHE is
still honored for backwards compatibility.

commit_message:
Update dib-run-parts

dib-run-parts in dib-utils had several fixes missing that had been
committed to diskimage-builder. When diskimage-builder switched to using
dib-run-parts from dib-utils, we lost these fixes. The switch over
happened in Ia0a0df7784a14c49b5c47ac0b03e6c2602c84b3b

These are the fixes from diskimage-builder that this commit adds back:
I44cf98dfc80cfcaec54b88cc83be80a3dbf2cec3
I24fd76c2b4f66b8036010b5079db39ead729abee
Iad2d490c86dceab148ea9ab08f457c49a5d5352e
Ieb48faacb4c96b7b358771d70c17f2f22d0354f4
Ia68853505485fefbf0890313456e7edb6097666b
Ibfb562c5970b40598fc95da1e8d4beb9d51d7612

Change-Id: Ice4b6a4b3d36a02099a682ae8cda4721211d51d9

Fix test failure in an lxc under osx

Adding a mock to prevent /proc/mounts lookup does
the trick of fixing the issue.

commit_message:
Fail on None before iteration attempt

Check for a 'None' value before trying to iterate over it
in the bulk code. Also eliminates an unneccessary anonymous
recursive function in the same bulk handling code.

Closes-Bug: #1368055

commit_message:
Fixes HyperV VM Console Log

This patch intends to fix some small nits introduced along with
the Nova console log patch.

The size of the console log can get bigger than expected because
of a small nit when checking the existing log file size as well
as a wrong size constant.

The method which gets the serial port pipe at the moment returns
a list which contains at most one element being the actual pipe
path. In order to avoid confusion this should return the pipe path
or None instead of a list.

Change-Id: I5ce9d1bea572f9098971990d011fa97ebf09233e
Closes-Bug: #1363899

commit_message:
Get instance_properties from request_spec

In NUMATopologyFilter instance_properties should
be retrived from request_spec which is embedded in
filter_properties and not from filter_properties
directly

Closes-bug: #1370068

Change-Id: If8f9464c6eb5451d0e21ddd14b072be3d2946c50

commit_message:
Set API_WORKERS to 2 by default

Devstack is usually used in environments with large numbers of CPUs and
large numbers of OpenStack services that default the number of api
workers to the number of CPUS. This commonly results in hitting memory
limits. Drop the number of API workers down to 2 by default.

Change-Id: I1c610c372a2e14ae23af7417960743f471ba1cd0

commit_message:
always set --no-hosts for dnsmasq

Many network modes in nova-network disable reading host entries from
/etc/hosts. This includes running vish-ha (multihost), or if you ever
set a dns server. However if you don't do these things we continue to
use /etc/hosts.

It's not clear that this does anything other than create
inconsistency. There is a long standing bug that exists around this
because the impacts include exposing localhost as a dns entry on the
network.

Change-Id: Ibccf0999bfd4b37f2d948af34640260f95c54572
Closes-Bug: #1201873

commit_message:
Make floatingip-ip-delete atomic with neutron

The infra guys were noticing an issue where they were leaking floating ip
addresses. One of the reasons this would occur for them is they called
nova floating-ip-delete which first disassocates the floating-ip in neutron
and then deletes it. Because nova-api makes two calls to neutron if the
first one succeeds and the second fails it results in the instance no longer
being associated with the floatingip. They have retry logic but they base it on
the instance and when they go to retry cleaning up the instance the floatingip
is no longer on the instance so they never delete it.

This patch fixes this issue by creating a new method
disassocate_and_delete_floating_ip which contains the different logic
needed to atomically do this for neutron rather than putting the logic
in the api layer to do something differently if one is using neutron.

This patch also adds additional code coverage for nova-network in the
delete floatingip case.

Closes-bug: 1356157

Conflicts:
	nova/api/openstack/compute/contrib/floating_ips.py
	nova/network/base_api.py

Change-Id: I53b0c9d949404288e8687b304361a74b53d69ef3
(cherry picked from commit 5f391087d1d75dd4e7532252c312256e9c3ea2b9)

commit_message:
Avoid re-adding iptables rules for instances that have disappeared

The remove_filters_for_instance() method fails silently if the
instance's chain is gone (i.e. it's been deleted). If this
happens while we're refreshing security group rules, we will
not notice this case and re-add stale rules for an old instance,
breaking our firewall for new instances.

This adds a quick check after we've captured the lock to see if
the associated chain exists, and bails if it doesn't.

Conflicts:
	nova/virt/firewall.py

Required changes:
- unit test was updated because in Havana, IptablesFirewallDriver has
  .instances instead of .instance_infos, and a separate .network_infos
  attribute.

Change-Id: Ic75988939f82de49735d85fe99a9eecd4baf45c9
Related-bug: #1182131
(cherry picked from commit 6aa368b99249d01f8fd7183c15d11986ad6a6fb7)
(cherry picked from commit 132d5a2064cfdc579a2e51f07e10e8eafbdf6327)

The encryption methods implemented for attached volumes
require a symbolic link created to the /dev/disk-by* iqn.

The current implementation works fine for LVM, however the rootwrap
is restricted to only allow iqns of the form openstack.org, for
vendors that use their own target and iqn this won't work and will

commit_message:
Fix rootwrap for non openstack.org iqn's

The encryption methods implemented for attached volumes
require a symbolic link created to the /dev/disk-by* iqn.

The current implementation works fine for LVM, however the rootwrap
is restricted to only allow iqns of the form openstack.org, for
vendors that use their own target and iqn this won't work and will
result in the attach failing for unauthorized command.

This just makes the regex for the rootwrap filter a bit more
permissive, only looking for iscsi-iqn.*

Change-Id: I023ad24867c045a88f72c5ac7ac4e4da097a3643
Closes-Bug: 1362854
(cherry picked from commit 00808f2072c3ee8958ad16eabad7994730bb8b86)

commit_message:
Fix incorrect root partition size and compatible volume name

When using rbd backend, it needs to resize volume size if size presents. Else
we will get wrong image size.

Rbd volume always uses uuid as the main pattern of volume name, now change to
it is necessary.

This patch also include a follow up fix of the original patch.
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/92512/

Fix bug 1219658

(cherry picked from commit 1b66a47b5f4cbcdf1a9a1ec38532474588a3fee2)

Conflicts:
	nova/virt/libvirt/imagebackend.py

Change-Id: I3dc8d639b066eac35d190b8d4687c41c9f4d5824

commit_message:
Use standard locale in list_partitions

parted function can output values which cannot be parsed by
_PARTED_PRINT_RE regexp in disk_partitioner module when using for
example ukrainian locale, as comma is used to separate integer and
fractional parts of float numbers. Standard 'C' locale should be used
to run parted.

Change-Id: Ic5b043796d548d91fb57a7ee34fe2e5a3a09088c
Closes-bug: #1371079

commit_message:
Debian: use libvirt-bin when needed

libvirtd is the new name of the init script in Debian testing.
libvirt-bin is still in use on Debian Wheezy.

Since I222b71962f49896063910ff2a25e4f57be4bf819, libvirtd is the
default for Debian, this break the compatibility with Debian Wheezy.

With this patch, we use libvirt-bin only if there is no
/etc/init.d/libvirtd init script.

Change-Id: I13694fef93d36c2e128e15e7dbfaec9230335585

commit_message:
Fixes NoneType vcpu list returned by Libvirt driver

* libvirt dom.vcpu may return a NoneType if vcpus dont exist

Change-Id: Iee10c2559ceea636bc4896595962e3470228ad35
Closes-Bug: #1274758
(cherry picked from commit 82821b407ce7a226918758876abca46b727d9706)

commit_message:
Mark nova-baremetal driver as deprecated in Juno, removed in K

This removes the old "untested and soon to be replaced" warning
to be in init_host() like other drivers, and with more details
(i.e. a timeline).

Change-Id: I251cad65b7ccf66733d8a626b1a50bfa58456e7f

commit_message:
Always filter out multicast from reflection

Instances will try IPv6 neighbour discovery via multicast
even in an IPv4-only cloud and can throw errors
if they see inbound packets from their own MAC address

Closes-bug: #1229625

Change-Id: I3539e788fe07519d87ce7c3800c5d38b7bd99d3b
(cherry picked from commit 9c044d2c94812e18cf84927fbf719cd073fe6c4f)

The code for this change looks good, but I have concerns regarding implementing such a restriction. AFAICT, Glance and Cinder allow creating images/volumes/snapshots without specifying the name. I just tried this using the command line tools, and was able to crate an image as well as volume without a name.

Since this behavior is allowed by their respective services, I don't think we should implement this restriction in Horizon. IIRC, we've already had similar patches in the past (patches which tried to add additional input constraints to Horizon, which were not present in the actual service) and the consensus was that Horizon is not the place to put these constraints.

I will let other cores chime in, but FWIW personally I don't think Horizon is the right place for constraints like this.

However, I agree there's an inconsistency in the way different pages display objects without a name (UUID vs blank space), so I would welcome a change which would introduce more consistency there. E.g. display the object's UUID if the name is missing."}, {'account_id': 11880, 'date': '2014-09-15 17:04:55.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 12:

Hi Ana, 

Thanks for the comments. However the bug is more of if user wants to put a name, put a name with something, don't put a name with just blank spaces. This is more of UX issue. Hope it makes sense. 

Gloria"}, {'account_id': 11880, 'date': '2014-09-15 21:31:54.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 12:

Hi Ana, 

I really appreciate your thoughts about this. I did some more thinking as well. Here are what I think:
 
First the name in the UI is already a required field in image, volume and volume type creation. 

Using id to replace the empty name in horizon is not an ideal solution either, because this makes the UI listing not consistent with the results of the backend command.

For example, currently, for image, we replaced the empty name with image id, UI shows image name is the id, while glance image-list command shows name is empty. If the image is bootable, when launch an instance from image in UI, the image shows up as id, I don't think it is useful from usability stand point. 

For volume type, volume and snapshot creation, currently we allow empty name shows up as an empty name. There are some ripple effects of the ugliness of the empty name. 

If we have a volume type with an empty name, when user creates a volume, you will see the "    " in the volume type selection list.

If we have a bootable volume with an empty name,  when user launches an instance using volume, you will see the empty name volume shows up in the selection list. 
.....

The fact that glance and cinder api allows empty names to go in doesn't mean it is user friendly. As far as I know for cinder, there is a bug https://bugs.launchpad.net/cinder/+bug/1206396 related to blank names. 

Horizon's goal is to improve the user experience, not just reflect what the back-end commands. Again, this is just my opinion. 

However entering empty name is just a corner case or a test case, I don't think most of the users want to enter an empty name for an image, or a volume or a volume type or a snapshot on purpose.

I will let the cores decide. Whatever cores decide, I am ok with that.

Gloria'}, {'account_id': 12000, 'date': '2014-09-15 21:55:45.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 12: Code-Review+1

commit_message:
Fixed issue of image name with only white spaces

Issues:
When user creates or edits image, specify the name with only
white spaces, the image shows up with image id.

When user creates or edits volume or snapshot or create volume type,
specify the name with only white spaces, the volume or volume types
shows up in the table with a name that looks like empty.

Fixes:
Added a validator validate_not_all_blank_value which checks the
value with only white spaces.

Update the name field in create/edit image form to use
validate_not_all_blank_value

Update the name field in create/edit volume, snapshot, create volume type
form to use validate_not_all_black_value

Closes-Bug: #1291414
Closes-Bug: #1357586

Change-Id: I94aec0d575faf9d9bac560222817518fdf7658a5

commit_message:
db: Add @_retry_on_deadlock to service_update()

Add the _retry_on_deadlock decorator to the service_update() method of
nova's sqlalchemy API.  This decorator is scattered throughout the
sqlalchemy API for other methods that may encounter this error.  The
referenced bug report shows a trace from where it occurred on this
method.

Change-Id: I93b370d6457d2e85493be01a62a76404d228a6fa
Closes-bug: #1370191
(cherry picked from commit 61d54f2652424279af81c4084e87651044fac4bd)

commit_message:
Update 'Configure Federation' documentation.

Apache 2.4 becomes more and more popular version of HTTP server.
With its release some options required for proper Shibboleth Service
Provider have changed. This patch updates information about ``ShibRequireAll``
options that is no longer valid under Apache 2.4. It also adds
documentation reference so users can read more about configuring Apache
Virtual Hosts along with Shibboleth Service Provider.

Change-Id: Idbec6690fd1d75f078a6bdcaa6388b885387b45d

sqlalchemy API for other methods that may encounter this error.  The

commit_message:
db: Add @_retry_on_deadlock to service_update()

Add the _retry_on_deadlock decorator to the service_update() method of
nova's sqlalchemy API.  This decorator is scattered throughout the
sqlalchemy API for other methods that may encounter this error.  The
referenced bug report shows a trace from where it occurred on this
method.

Change-Id: I93b370d6457d2e85493be01a62a76404d228a6fa
Closes-bug: #1370191
(cherry picked from commit 61d54f2652424279af81c4084e87651044fac4bd)

commit_message:
Require tests for DB migrations

This patch makes it mandatory to have at least a check routine for each migration.
Some migrations are special (like the compressed one at the beginning, and the
placeholder migrations), and can be skipped. Also, all baremetal migrations are
excepted from this policy since that code is deprecated and needs to go away soon.

Change-Id: Id8c10d5ea3d8a8864a32ea4b0f0b94657e1e9bf7
Closes-Bug: #1370536

Feel like we're missing some cases here, for example copy_image_to_volume, maybe some others.

I still wonder if we couldn't just add this to the create itself, both volume and snapshot and just be done with it.  In other words have all of this happen in cinder.brick.local_dev.lvm in the create methods?  I am still bothered about having multiple patches for this and having the calls spread out through all of the different modules."}, {'account_id': 2243, 'date': '2014-01-31 04:30:56.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Do not merge

I'd rather not backport this til we determine we're actually done with this activation craziness and we have a clean method of doing it."}, {'account_id': 2243, 'date': '2014-01-31 05:18:52.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

By the way, happy to remove the -2 I just wanted to make sure I sync up with you before this goes through.'}, {'account_id': 4523, 'date': '2014-01-31 15:33:29.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

There hasn't yet been a strong case made for manually activating volumes.  Every platform we run on automatically activates them.  We should probably look into this for general safety against odd configurations but it's not a pressing issue, and probably not worth a Havana backport as of now.  (Bug 1271971)  Not activating snaps means things are broken on sufficiently new versions of LVM.

I am currently against activating snapshots at creation time.  LVM upstream has changed the behavior in recent versions of LVM2 to not automatically activate thin snaps.  They are also, by default, tagged with a "skip activation" flag which we would have to clear if we activated them at creation time -- otherwise rebooting would break things.

We could do all of this but I assume they are saving resources (or have some similar justification) by not having them all active by default and it isn't obvious why we'd want to do something different when activating at time-of-use works well.'}, {'account_id': 2243, 'date': '2014-01-31 16:23:52.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: No score

Thanks Eric, so I have some issues with your statement "it was changed for a reason" however I can't find any data specifying 'why'.

Also it seems that Suse and some other distros have made the default setting be to activate for non-root volumes.  I really don't know the details but for sure we need to investigate this and figure it out.

Frankly I see no advantage of doing this at this point at all.  It really to me just seems to make the code more complex and harder to follow what's going on, and because the operation is in random places like it is it introduces a significant bug potential IMO.'}, {'account_id': 1420, 'date': '2014-03-28 02:26:49.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Do not merge

commit_message:
LVM: Activate source snap LV when cloning from volume

Similar to the change made in:
01a2199 LVM: Activate source LV before cloning from it

Previous change only fixed this issue for clone-from-snapshot.

This activates the source snapshot LV when cloning from volume
as well, fixing the problem where cloning fails due to inability
to open the source LV device.

Related-Bug: 1252423
Closes-Bug: 1260786

(cherry picked from commit 673057320929d33095c998d477c2537567ccf74b)

Change-Id: If48be8516fd71738cb83a91683c33d02f227b9d6

commit_message:
Add Hyper-V driver in the "compute_driver" option description

The description of the option "compute_driver" should include
hyperv.HyperVDriver along with the other supported driver.

Conflicts:
        nova/virt/driver.py
        nova/virt/hyperv/__init__.py

Closes-bug: #1347777
(cherry picked from commit b856bc5e348cc69923e3ee815303804323730026)

Change-Id: Ic7e16fd5154609987b2ef0b6f8ee52619ccf489c

commit_message:
Glance: Add RBD to known_stores when Ceph is enabled

If the Ceph service is enabled, ensure the RBD store
is added to the list of known_stores for Glance.

If missing, you will see an error like:
 ERROR: Store for scheme rbd not found

Change-Id: I93033b55ef0ac3356a18cd38a34fd92da407c3f7

[{'created': '2014-09-07 22:25:47.000000000', 'message': "Fix tempest.scenario.manager.ScenarioTest

Add logic to tempest.scenario.manager.ScenarioTest to translate, when creating
a server, a networks specification in the format
'nics': [{'net-id': '<net-uuid>'}] to the format
'networks': [{'uuid': '<net-uuid>'}], which is what the tempest servers client
can handle

Change-Id: I6d05e0ebed23b3d49df51020f86c244f1d606644
Closes-Bug: 1366623
"}, {'created': '2014-09-11 00:38:00.000000000', 'message': "Fix tempest.scenario.manager.ScenarioTest

Modifies create_server method to specify network to be connected to server when
caller doesn't specify one

Change-Id: I6d05e0ebed23b3d49df51020f86c244f1d606644
Closes-Bug: 1366623
"}]
commit_message:
Fix tempest.scenario.manager.ScenarioTest

Modifies create_server method to specify network to be connected to server when
caller doesn't specify one

Change-Id: I6d05e0ebed23b3d49df51020f86c244f1d606644
Closes-Bug: 1366623

commit_message:
Save files while updating a template.

When updating a template object, any updates to the files must also be
saved in the database. With this change, updates to files of a template
are also saved in database.

Change-Id: Ia5b84780158c47ffe807829ce2fc83f4ffbb6db3

commit_message:
Check for ports in subnet before deleting it from Nuage VSD

There could exist a port in subnet in neutron in which case subnet delete
is not allowed. In the nuage's plugin code, this validation needs to
be handle prior to sending delete subnet request to backend.

Change-Id: Idd20d2f878a6274a012504108d01bd2237dc665a
Closes-bug: #1351522

commit_message:
Use string.ascii_letters to be python 3 compatible

Use string.ascii_letters instead of string.letter. The only consequence
is to loose the locale-specific behavior but it seems not to be a bad
thing for generating a secret key.

Change-Id: Id985d798042eaa7541692d137027233537ed3bb4

commit_message:
Change unit string translation in volume limit templates

This fixes an issue where the lazy translated "GB" unit string is
not properly resolved in the volume limit templates. This error
does not happen in a devstack environment but has been found to
happen in chef and puppet deployed OpenStack production
environments.

Closes-Bug: 1332238
Change-Id: Icc056ca508f430e981049ca00985d329c92a6ab4

commit_message:
Workaround for negative vals in total*Used in nova absolute_limits

Due to bug 1370867 there is a case where negative values are returned
in total*Used in absolute_limits. If it occurs, Horizon Overview page
cannot be displayed due to an error "cannot convert float infinity to
integer". This commit replaces negative values in total*Used with 0
for a workarond.

Change-Id: I606803bdff1d335cc9f92d67619ff82f356a5143
Closes-Bug: #1370869

commit_message:
Modified docs to list supported browsers

As reported in the bug, the documentation needs to be updated with
a list of browsers we support. This patch adds faq entry and updates
information for contributing.

Change-Id: I6218194d031bc6b47a0fd13e5e11749df441398b
Closes-Bug: 1359246

Give size field default value (Create Volume)

Minimum size for volume is 1GB so this is the default value for the size field
on the create volume modal

Change-Id: Ifeaf45ff24cb4b95c9898fc1f92debe9a17ea319
Closes-bug: 1370450

commit_message:
Fixed add_bootstrap_class template filter

Made sure that the add_bootstrap_class filter correctly obtains the
widget type to prevent it applying the form-control css class onto
parts of forms that shouldn't have it.

Change-Id: I307780b241e70de38e405cbffc4a35859b9aaf1b
Closes-Bug: 1367302

[{'created': '2014-09-15 09:34:34.000000000', 'message': 'Show floating IP associated with Load Balancer VIP

Previously the code always tried to show an instance when
a floating IP is associated. This commit chnages the code
to consider a port device_owner associated with a floating IP
so that appropriate information is displayed in the table.

Change-Id: I5d99090b17bf94a80a0d7894ab2084f83e55d59d
Closes-Bug: #1359215
'}]
commit_message:
Show floating IP associated with Load Balancer VIP

Previously the code always tried to show an instance when
a floating IP is associated. This commit chnages the code
to consider a port device_owner associated with a floating IP
so that appropriate information is displayed in the table.

Change-Id: I5d99090b17bf94a80a0d7894ab2084f83e55d59d
Closes-Bug: #1359215

commit_message:
Move cacert/insecure awkwardness examples/common

The requests.Session object that transport derives from has
this overloaded meaning for verify that is causing awkwardness
around our code.  I've moved the ugly to the examples/common.py
argument parsing.

Change-Id: I3e8f5311eeba6108d3ea086a01b71663401a52fa

Testr pumps out a lot of output to the screen even
with successful tests. Other OpenStack projects
solve this by modifying their testr config to force
stdout and stderr capture similar to other testing

Change-Id: Ie6fb60585a632e09fef068f768c6b6fde10017f0
'}]
commit_message:
Modifying testr conf to suppress output

Testr pumps out a lot of output to the screen even
with successful tests. Other OpenStack projects
solve this by modifying their testr config to force
stdout and stderr capture similar to other testing
frameworks. For this change, I have copied how
Nova handles this.

Change-Id: Ie6fb60585a632e09fef068f768c6b6fde10017f0

commit_message:
Update cinder.conf permission

cinder.conf contains some secret information such as qpid password.
To prevent unauthorized users to access it, this file should be set
as 640 mode.

Fix bug 1369467
Change-Id: I12a0e6e3e492397f1282366ab38ed1e1f46997f7

commit_message:
Correct incorrect reference to importutils.import_object

Ceilometer has been switched to use oslo.utils. But different with
class ceilometer.openstack.common.importutils,
oslo.utils.importutils does have the definition of method
import_object. Instead, it only has method _import_object defined.
This commit updates ceilometer/cmd/alarm.py to fix the import
error.

Bug:#1362006

Change-Id: Ibfc75aa3d8e5187b36291b902ac764a9fea62b19

commit_message:
L3 Metering label as shared

With this patch metering labels can be set
as shared so that the rules associated with
this label will be applied to all routers for
all tenants.

Also changed all attributes on metering labels
to not allow updates ('allow_put': False),
since there are no update methods.

Partially implements
blueprint l3-metering-mgnt-ext

DocImpact

Change-Id: Ice405585fc50786d52eecc35c01605ac0e9550ac

And if we did go the route of how Heat does this, I'd actually think it's more blueprint type area for that kind of refactor more than a bug fix, which is what this is trying to be (and keeping in mind that we want to be able to bakcport this to stable/icehouse since we have no ssl support for glance via nova in stable/icehouse right now)."}, {'account_id': 5638, 'date': '2014-05-01 15:09:57.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 7:

I certainly prefer the approach of having one single CA option rather than one for each service, though I do wonder if there is a valid use case which would require different CAs to be used for different services ?

A 3rd possibility would be to only have a fixed CA cert to use for contacting a cert distribution service (Keystone?), and then Nova could dynamically request the CA certs for other services it needed to talk to. This would allow for  services to have different CA certs if needed without creating a huge burden in the per-host config files.

Overall I'm inclined to agree with @dims that this change merits a blueprint in nova-specs to examine the various options open to us."}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-05-23 12:32:20.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 7: -Verified

commit_message:
Adds CA cert file path option for glance connections

Currently, there is no way to pass CA cert for HTTPS glance
connections.

A new global 'ca_certificates_file' option is used for glance
and will be used for neutron and cinder CA cert file paths
if specified and the existing service-specific CA cert file
path options are not used.

Deprecates neutron_ca_certificates_file and
cinder_ca_certificates_file options in favor of the new global
cross-service ca_certificates_file option. The old options
may be removed in the 2015.1 release.

Closes-Bug: #1299841

DocImpact - New option 'ca_certificates_file' added to
            nova.conf; deprecated neutron_ca_certificates_file
            and cinder_ca_certificates_file options.

Co-authored-by: Matt Riedemann <mriedem@us.ibm.com>
Change-Id: Id751fad65685ef1c75555e21497200027f3f11d4

Sure no problem.  I'm in the process of creating a full integration test framework leveraging test-kitchen and kitchen-openstack in a lab we have here at Chef.  Right now we have no way of knowing what changes effects just a basic full test. Yes, we have unit/acceptance testing, but we don't have anything that puts it all together.

That's my goal, a Jenkins build of everything,  something like [1], so when someone puts a review in we have at least a sign off that you can still get a minimum viable working compute cluster.
I've did some manual simple test with this fixes. Refer to https://bugs.launchpad.net/openstack-chef/+bug/1369411.

commit_message:
Update neutron.conf permission

To avoid other users to access scecret in neutron.conf, set the
file permission to 640 instead of 644

Fix bug 1369455

Change-Id: Ied4bd43ed3ecdfdb97d3b7be10b8af9548d4e762

rng_dev_path in nova.conf template configurable in node attribute

added attribute to make rng_dev_path in nova.conf configurable with the
node attribute default['openstack']['compute']['libvirt']['rng_dev_path']. Default is set to nil to let this parameter stay an optional one.

Change-Id: I1bcf67eec0b8918a3ba644d76cafb20ab89ce704

commit_message:
Update heat.conf permission

To avoid unauthorized users to read secrete information in
heat.conf, heat.conf should be set as 640 instead of 644.

Fix bug 1370870
Change-Id: I02756cea10113ca89ddeaa9232d04c75380756e8

[{'created': '2014-09-03 14:32:48.000000000', 'message': 'Set mysql root password directly on resource

Set the mysqll root password directly on the server resource, so it
does not need to be an attribute.  This keeps passwords sourced from
encrypted data bags out of node attributes. Note that as indicated
in https://github.com/opscode-cookbooks/mysql/issues/215 all recipes
will be removed from the mysql cookbook in favor of having consumers
work with the resources directly, thereby providing more flexibility
in terms of how the various configuration settings are sourced.

Change-Id: I72be1e2131a107ddc43754bc5cf40a4ce7face95
'}, {'created': '2014-09-03 14:47:26.000000000', 'message': 'Set mysql root password directly on resource

in terms of how the various configuration settings are sourced.

commit_message:
Set mysql root password directly on resource

Set the mysql root password directly on the server resource, so it
does not need to be an attribute.  This keeps passwords sourced from
encrypted data bags out of node attributes. Note that as indicated
in https://github.com/opscode-cookbooks/mysql/issues/215 all recipes
will be removed from the mysql cookbook in favor of having consumers
work with the resources directly, thereby providing more flexibility
in terms of how the various configuration settings are sourced.
Including the "server" recipe is not going to be a viable option
once that has happened, so this change not only addresses the
attribute issue, but it will also make upcoming changes to the
mysql cookbook more seamless.  Note that the reference to the
default_version_for function had to be removed, because it is no
longer in the cookbook and therefore the build failed. It is no
longer necessary to set the version, as described in the README.md
file:

When [the version parameter is] omitted, it will install the
default MySQL version for the target platform.

Note that the code that sets node attributes in
spec/mysql-server_spec.rb was removed because it was interfering
with the new test and it did not seem to serve any purpose--there
were no failures after it was removed.

blueprint no-secret-attributes

Change-Id: I72be1e2131a107ddc43754bc5cf40a4ce7face95

subject: Update requests to have a hard lower limit of 2.4.1
messages:
[{'account_id': 12000, 'date': '2014-09-11 20:12:22.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 6873, 'date': '2014-09-11 21:16:42.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

I think we're in dependency freeze and this is pretty risky at this point since the clients are using requests and I think some of them are already cutting their final releases before rc1 - but have a due date of 9/18 for their final final releases I guess.

The bug looks pretty bad though...so maybe there is an exception here, but we'd really need to get this burned in as soon as possible."}, {'account_id': 12000, 'date': '2014-09-11 21:20:09.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

I'm willing to wait to land this patchset and it's the actual fix in novaclient. This was just the earliest possible moment that I could realistically write these patches (since it took a long time for requests 2.4.x to land with the appropriate version of urllib3. I'll maintain these until the timing is better."}, {'account_id': 6873, 'date': '2014-09-11 21:30:53.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

2.3.0 CVE's fixed:

https://pypi.python.org/pypi/requests/2.3.0

No longer expose Authorization or Proxy-Authorization headers on redirect. commit_message:
Update requests to have a hard lower limit of 2.4.1

This prevents anything less than 2.3.0 from being installed. 2.3.0
contains fixes for two CVEs. 2.4.1 adds support for setting custom
socket options before opening a connection which is necessary in
some OpenStack clients (e.g., to enable TCP Keep-Alive).

Related-bug: 1323862
Change-Id: I6694c5e952138da865c5de8ac09e3a98e5625f08

Checking specific mistakes can be automated via hacking rules.

This patch:
 * adds HACKING.rst - list of rules;
 * adds rally.hacking - module for implementation of rules;
 * edits tox.ini, so hacking rules will be checked during pep8 test;
 * adds 3 rules related to mistakes in  `assert_*` methods from `mock`
   library. Also tests, which are failed due to these rules, are fixed.

commit_message:
Change "Cinder" to "OpenStack Block Storage"

In a commit yesterday (https://review.openstack.org/#/c/122302/), I
didn't follow the doc guidelines and used the term Cinder. This fixes
this snafoo.

 the downgrade.

commit_message:
Correct intent of function names in nodes

_create_or_register_{bm,ironic}_node does not express the intent
of the function, since creating a node is the same as registering it.
Fix this thinko by calling the functions
_update_or_register_{bm,ironic}_node.

Change-Id: Ifa5932b78a103655885af3742eeda8156b457822

[{'created': '2014-09-18 02:34:59.000000000', 'message': "Stop creating extraneous directories

Cannot help streamlining the code a bit, sorry. But the meat is that
we should not try to make directories if output path is explicit.

Previously we created directories using the URL path, which is
obviously wrong if explicit output file is supplied... unless
a crafty user supplied the same path with -o that is contained
in the URL path. If anyone was doing such tricks, it's not going
to work anymore (we are forcing a regression for the sake of
theoretical correctness here).

Fixes bug: 1369546

Change-Id: Ifce31f2ba233eb55550f3810348bf16bf2447d62
"}]
commit_message:
Stop creating extraneous directories

Cannot help streamlining the code a bit, sorry. But the meat is that
we should not try to make directories if output path is explicit.

Previously we created directories using the URL path, which is
obviously wrong if explicit output file is supplied... unless
a crafty user supplied the same path with -o that is contained
in the URL path. If anyone was doing such tricks, it's not going
to work anymore (we are forcing a regression for the sake of
theoretical correctness here).

Fixes bug: 1369546

Change-Id: Ifce31f2ba233eb55550f3810348bf16bf2447d62

commit_message:
Set postgresql max_connections=151

Now that we have multiple workers running by default
in various projects (nova/cinder/glance/trove), the
postgresql job is failing intermittently with connection
failures to the database.

The default max_connections for postgresql is 100 so here
we double that.

Note that the default max_connections for mysql used to
be 100 but is now 151, so this change brings the postgresql
configuration more in line with mysql.

Change-Id: I2fcae8184a82e303103795a7bf57c723e27190c9
Closes-Bug: #1338841
(cherry picked from commit 94c654ef37f6a0247a307578f3240f97201a3cba)

[{'created': '2014-08-21 16:13:57.000000000', 'message': "Remove the Cisco Nexus monolithic plugin as ml2 driver takes it place

The Cisco Nexus monolithic plugin does not work without the Open
vSwitch plugin. The Open vSwitch plugin is scheduled to be removed
as per #1323729. This patch removes the Nexus Hardware switch
related plugin code. The N1KV virtual switch related code will
still remain in the tree as it doesn't depend on Open vSwitch
plugin.

Closes-Bug: #1350387
Change-Id: I2542e92c25e9280e975c3903afb9114e850a966a

commit_message:
Remove the Cisco Nexus monolithic plugin

The Cisco Nexus monolithic plugin does not work without the Open
vSwitch plugin. The Open vSwitch plugin is scheduled to be removed
as per #1323729. This patch removes the Nexus Hardware switch
related plugin code. The N1KV virtual switch related code will
still remain in the tree as it doesn't depend on Open vSwitch
plugin.

Closes-Bug: #1350387
Change-Id: I2542e92c25e9280e975c3903afb9114e850a966a

commit_message:
Use OpenStack incubated branding

Since designate is an incubated project, it should use the incubated
OpenStack branding.

Update also requirements.txt from global requirements file for needed
requirements.

commit_message:
Add API integration tests for v2

- Added integration tests for API version 2
- Refactor base.py, separate methods for v1 and v2
- Created second endpoint /v2 in keystone in devstack installation

Change-Id: Ibe23971b2335242ed72b837bfc1f861d0a74e395

commit_message:
Fix client tests due to changes in code from 'mistral' repository

-Removing 'start-task' parameter from test workbooks
-Lowercase key section names in workbooks from unit tests
-Rename 'test_cli_acitons' to 'test_cli_actions'
-Fix CLI test 'test_task_list' due to changes in
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/121818/

Change-Id: I8ace89b460c3c72cdac3c3f42684fe1e8b6ad5de

commit_message:
Update doc for qos_policy_group NetApp extra spec

Bug 1288283 updated the function behind the qos_policy_group extra spec,
but the docs were never updated to reflect the change in behavior from
being a capability advertised to the scheduler to being a directive that
needed to be executed post provisioning.

Change-Id: Ia91a7cde1e0c9343de682d7b30a9898c6319ae8b

commit_message:
node_uuid should not be used to create test port

Some tests pass node_uuid to create_test_port function, while it is
not port attribute and is ignored. node_id is passed instead.

Change-Id: I06ccca8a08d500bd67d6e85094604bb0bd24a851

commit_message:
Be more tolerant of unicode exceptions

When an exception message is in unicode we should not fail
when trying to get that unicode containing exceptions message
so instead of using str() use a new utils function that has
been working in other projects to attempt to convert a exception
message into its corresponding unicode in a safer manner.

Change-Id: I202f12d8f9bf562972b760f91805dba2ad14d804

[{'created': '2014-09-12 21:34:34.000000000', 'message': 'Ensure identity sql driver supports domain-specific configuration.

For an identity driver to be used with a domain-specific config file,
it must accept a ConfigOpts as an optional parameter. The ldap driver
already supported this - so this patch adds this to the sql driver.

The above change is trivial, but the rest of the patch is enhancing
our testing to validate this operation.

Closes-Bug: 1217017
Change-Id: Ic531ebae28680fc518d8e036db516f5982241c40
'}, {'created': '2014-09-12 21:54:14.000000000', 'message': 'Ensure identity sql driver supports domain-specific configuration.

For an identity driver to be used with a domain-specific config file,
it must accept a ConfigOpts as an optional parameter. The ldap driver
already supported this - so this patch adds this to the sql driver.

The above change is trivial, but the rest of the patch is enhancing
our testing to validate this operation.

Limitations:

This patch only enables, as indicated in the configuration docs, a
single SQL backend to be used (e.g. only one domain-specifc config
file referencing the identity sql driver). This allows for the
(often requested) scenario of service users to be stored in SQL in
a predominantly LDAP installation.  Follow-on patches may remove
this restriction.

Closes-Bug: 1217017
Change-Id: Ic531ebae28680fc518d8e036db516f5982241c40

'}, {'created': '2014-09-16 17:59:28.000000000', 'message': 'Ensure identity sql driver supports domain-specific configuration.

For an identity driver to be used with a domain-specific config file,
it must accept a ConfigOpts as an optional parameter. The ldap driver
already supported this - so this patch adds this to the sql driver.

The above change is trivial, but the rest of the patch is enhancing
our testing to validate this operation, as well as enforcing the
limitation listed below.

Limitation:

Currently Keystone only supports one SQL driver - this patch
does not change that.  What it does enable is for that one SQL
driver to be assigned to a specific domain, as opposed to being just
a catch-all for domains without a specific configuration file.
This at least enables the (often requested) scenario of service users
to be stored in SQL in a predominantly LDAP installation.

Closes-Bug: 1217017
Change-Id: Ic531ebae28680fc518d8e036db516f5982241c40

commit_message:
Ensure identity sql driver supports domain-specific configuration.

For an identity driver to be used with a domain-specific config file,
it must accept a ConfigOpts as an optional parameter. The ldap driver
already supported this - so this patch adds this to the sql driver.

The above change is trivial, but the rest of the patch is enhancing
our testing to validate this operation, as well as enforcing the
limitation listed below.

Limitation:

Currently Keystone only supports one SQL driver - this patch
does not change that.  What it does enable is for that one SQL
driver to be assigned to a specific domain, as opposed to being just
a catch-all for domains without a specific configuration file.
This at least enables the (often requested) scenario of service users
to be stored in SQL in a predominantly LDAP installation.

Closes-Bug: 1217017
Change-Id: Ic531ebae28680fc518d8e036db516f5982241c40

Update horizon conf file permission

To avoid unauthorized users to acquire secrete in configuration
file, set the files contain password from 0644 to 0640
Fix bug 1370888

commit_message:
Move multipart MIME parser into utils

Over on the EC branch, we need to be able to parse multipart MIME
documents in the object server. The formpost middleware has a
perfectly good MIME parser, but it seems sort of awful to import
things from formpost in swift/obj/server.py, so I pulled it out into
common.utils.

Change-Id: Ieb4c05d02d8e4ef51a3a11d26c503786b1897f60

This fix apparently broke it

Added the dict to unit-tests.

commit_message:
Assume VNIC_NORMAL if binding:vnic_type not set

Nova was assuming that every port returned from neutron had a
binding:vnic_type attribute, however this is not always the case.
This fix ensures that in the cases when a port does not have the
attribute nova assumes the default, VNIC_NORMAL. Unit tests added
to prevent the regression of this change have also been addded.

Change-Id: Ia92ffa8658c2e972fa5556e9e47ada8affb57053
Closes-Bug: 1370077

It looks so weird. I can reproduce the failure in Enderbury timezone.
Is it a possible bug in Python time and datetime standard library?
Supposedly we are using naive datetime which is not aware of timezone info. But it seems that datetime.datetime.strftime() return a value with timezone offset. When I refer to the strftime(3) documentation on Linux manual (http://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man3/strftime.3.html), it says the format '%s' will return "The number of seconds since the Epoch, 1970-01-01 00:00:00  +0000 (UTC). (TZ)". So I think the strftime() function might be misunderstood here which means it is timezone awareness based on its implementation.'}, {'account_id': 2622, 'date': '2014-08-29 21:49:08.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-2

Yes, I think there's a real bug in the last_modified_date_to_timestamp() function. If it can return anything besides 0.0 for '1970-01-01T00:00:00.000000', something's gone horribly wrong. The date from the container listing is in UTC, and Unix epoch times are always UTC as well.

I don't believe we should update the test to encode the incorrect behavior."}, {'account_id': 2649, 'date': '2014-09-01 02:33:41.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

@Samuel, agree with you. It doesn't make sense to fix the test. close it would be right choice."}, {'account_id': 2622, 'date': '2014-09-18 16:09:05.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned

if I'm wrong, there's a "Restore Change" button that'll undo this; please push it if you want this change back'}]

commit_message:
Fix test_last_modified_date_to_timestamp unware of timezone

Due to different local timezone setting, this test case failed to
assert equal time. add time.timezone to fix the gap of seconds.

Fixes Bug #1341415

commit_message:
Add quotes for bareword instances of 'type'

In Puppet 3.7.x, 'type' is now a reserved word.  So it must
be quoted to avoid reserved word usage errors.

Closes-Bug: 1370748

Change-Id: I3bb9b0482baebdce549faa1aaf2b0f6073c95e90

[{'created': '2014-07-25 14:01:16.000000000', 'message': "virt: use compute.vm_mode constants and validate vm mode type

Where we have hardcoded vm modes, use compute.vm_mode constants.

commit_message:
virt: use compute.vm_mode constants and validate vm mode type

Where we have hardcoded vm modes, use compute.vm_mode constants.
Where we get vm modes from external systems, validate them against
the list of acceptable names.

The baremetal/ironic drivers are reporting a bogus vm mode of
'baremetal' for supported instances which is confusing the vm
mode with the Nova driver type. These drivers use the native
ABI for their architecture, so should be reporting 'hvm' as
the vm mode, which indicates an unmodified native OS ABI.

On the other side, the ImagePropertiesFilter will canonicalize
the hvtype it fetches from image metadata, so that 'baremetal'
gets remapped to 'hvm' during comparison.

Closes-bug: #1348629

commit_message:
Install tempest-lib as part of install_tempest

This commit adds support to devstack to install the newly created
tempest-lib project.

Change-Id: Ifcf56639757ec4814dcd31f791931afe61f5a672

commit_message:
Update oslo.messaging to latest version

Fixes from 1.4.0.0a3 to 1.4.0.0a5 include:
6ea3b12 Imported Translations from Transifex
fbee941 An initial implementation of an AMQP 1.0 based messaging driver
a9ec73f Switch to oslo.utils
48a9ba4 Fix Python 3 testing
265b21f Import oslo-incubator context module
f480494 Import oslo-incubator/middleware/base
7381ccd Should not send replies for cast messages
4cb33ec Port to Python 3
710dd17 Sync jsonutils from oslo-incubator
2464ca0 Add parameter to customize Qpid receiver capacity
220ccb8 Make tests pass with random python hashseed
92d5679 Set sample_default for rpc_zmq_host
dd1d6d1 Enable PEP8 check E714
ec9ffdb Enable PEP8 check E265
8151da8 Enable PEP8 check E241
ba5b547 Fix error in example of an RPC server
7fdedda Replace lambda method _
500f1e5 Enable check for E226
63a6d62 Updated from global requirements
bea9723 Add release notes for 1.4.0.0a4
d020cb8 Add release notes for stable/icehouse 1.3.1 release
5be1b6a Enabled hacking checks H305 and H307
6684565 Bump hacking to version 0.9.2
1cc3e5d Fixes incorrect exchange lock in fake driver
39d1917 Imported Translations from Transifex
5fbb55b Add missing docs for list_opts()
503b48a Synced jsonutils and its dependencies from oslo-incubator

Change-Id: I1340127f8dac98912170ed0c8d70ec2fa9c89f8c

commit_message:
Make class setup safe in compute base admin class

The setup class in BaseComputeAdminTest is not safe - it may
leak isolated credentials. If there is a failure during setup
the class teardown is not invoked.

Change-Id: Id58c5460ac661e1814943b48730eae359c8f960a

commit_message:
Synced jsonutils from oslo-incubator

The sync includes change that drastically enhances performance on Python
2.6 with fresh simplejson library installed.

Included commits:
* jsonutils.py:
  - 1b901885: Enforce unicode json output for jsonutils.load[s]()
  - cd909d83: jsonutils.load() accepts file pointer, not string
  - d14f56f0: On Python <= 2.6, use simplejson if available

This change also introduces new incubator module 'strutils' that is used
by jsonutils now.

Conflicts:
	neutron/openstack/common/jsonutils.py

Change-Id: Ief94101488214ddf93c3547a9c50134826b9b165
Closes-Bug: 1314129
(cherry picked from commit 8131a2eca838d1cb584646615e48fc11d8a90571)

commit_message:
bring over pretty_tox.sh from tempest

Tempest developed a set of wrappers around testr to print out tests as
they are running through using the subunit stream. This also displays
which workers the various tests are running on. Adapted for nova's
need for loading the locking.

I expect that the needs of nova will diverge this over time,
especially what's displayed during tracing, as such I think it's fine
to just do a transplant and not try to turn this into some external
repo.

Change-Id: Ied1708515fc49f4e18cd8dbb7b2cd821f85e1966

Keystone should stop testing using keystoneclient... I thought we'd do that as part of getting rid of v2 but now I'm not sure when that's going to happen."}, {'account_id': 9656, 'date': '2014-08-19 08:41:14.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

As I told in another (havana) backport, I would prefer devstack to install oslo.utils from master instead of putting it in project dependencies everywhere the client module is used.'}, {'account_id': 6486, 'date': '2014-08-25 00:15:08.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

Ihar - It's only used in keystone."}, {'account_id': 9656, 'date': '2014-09-08 10:54:24.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

@Brant, so?.. I think we may still install oslo.utils from master in gate without overpopulating our stable branches with fake dependencies.'}, {'account_id': 6486, 'date': '2014-09-08 19:01:06.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

Ihar - It's not a fake dependency. Keystone's unit tests will depend on oslo.utils being there."}, {'account_id': 9656, 'date': '2014-09-11 09:00:21.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

Keystone depends on oslo.utils *just* because devstack installs keystoneclient incorrectly (doing git clone without providing all its dependencies). I think it's not the excuse to fix keystone, it's a proposal to fix devstack to install oslo.utils for us."}, {'account_id': 9656, 'date': '2014-09-12 14:16:33.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

For Icehouse, I've cherry-picked the appropriate devstack change: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/121128/ I guess that we won't need to insert that new testing dependency once the patch reaches the tree."}, {'account_id': 6486, 'date': '2014-09-12 15:02:24.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

Only changing devstack makes the assumption that everyone is using devstack. Not everyone uses devstack.'}, {'account_id': 9656, 'date': '2014-09-12 15:26:27.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

@Brent, I've finally looked at those failures you try to solve, and I believe that those patches are not needed at all.

So the scenario of failure goes as follows:
- devstack installs keystoneclient;
- it syncs global requirements file from openstack/requirements to keystoneclient;
- then it calls pip install -e for the client.

Since at the moment of failures, Havana and Icehouse openstack/requirements branches didn't have oslo.utils in it, that dependency was removed by step 2, and was not installed.

But now that global requirements contain that dep in both branches, everything should work as-is.

So I believe the patch is just not-needed as global requirements update was enough."}, {'account_id': 6476, 'date': '2014-09-12 17:15:16.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1

Ihar, please don't consider only the gate here. If Keystone is to use oslo.utils, then it should declare it, so that us, package maintainers for distributions, have a clear pictures of what type of dependency the package should have. FYI, I always do a diff from one version to the next to see what has changed. If Keystone uses oslo.utils and before it didn't, but there's no change in the requirements.txt, then I simply will miss the fact, and have dependencies wrong in my package."}, {'account_id': 2903, 'date': '2014-09-13 03:03:39.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

@Thomas Goirand, This is an issue where the new keystoneclient requires oslo.utils and keystone tests depend on the keystoneclient (in a weird way). The real solution (long term, but wont work for icehouse) will be to ensure we stop doing the checkout/run of keystoneclient in this way against keystone during testing.

It has long been on the list of things we need to resolve in our testing, but for the stable/* branches it's hard to "fix" it.'}, {'account_id': 9656, 'date': '2014-09-15 08:14:38.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

@Thomas, I agree with what you say (me being a package maintainer, that's no doubt we need to have straight requirements). That said, this is not the case: here, keystone does not use oslo.utils, but keystoneclient that is used by keystone, does. So the dependency belongs to keystoneclient, not keystone.

Also, I think the patch is not needed since the issue that it was triggered by is already fixed in affected branches."}, {'account_id': 6476, 'date': '2014-09-15 08:44:05.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1

Ihar, if that's the case, then I am voting -1 instead of +1. Indeed, I see no reason why a dependency in the client would land in the server, it makes no sense to me either."}, {'account_id': 6486, 'date': '2014-09-18 13:39:44.000000000', 'content': "Abandoned

This shouldn't be needed anymore."}]

commit_message:
add oslo.utils for testing with Keystoneclient master

stable/* tests run with keystoneclient master and
master keystoneclient will be changing to require
oslo.utils.

Change-Id: Ia29f69731d4dc79e8fc5d14afa932558de387799
Closes-Bug: #1357652

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-01-18 02:35:50.000000000', 'message': "Add context as parameter for two libvirt APIs

When finish_revert_migration is called, the caller of
finish_revert_migration already includes context as a parameter,
but finish_revert_migration did not reuse this parameter and still
re-generate the context inside finish_revert_migration, we should
add context as a new parameter for finish_revert_migration so that
the functions inside of it can reuse context when needed.

For the function _create_domain_and_network in libvirt/driver.py,
it set context as an optional parameter, but context isn't really
an optional parameter for this method. We should always pass a
context down because it might be needed somewhere inside

commit_message:
Add context as parameter for two libvirt APIs

When finish_revert_migration is called, the caller of
finish_revert_migration already includes context as a parameter,
but finish_revert_migration did not reuse this parameter and still
re-generate the context inside finish_revert_migration, we should
add context as a new parameter for finish_revert_migration so that
the functions inside of it can reuse context when needed.

For the function _create_domain_and_network in libvirt/driver.py,
it set context as an optional parameter, but context isn't really
an optional parameter for this method. We should always pass a
context down because it might be needed somewhere inside
_create_domain_and_network().

The patch includes two parts:
1) Add context as a new parameter for finish_revert_migration
2) Set context as a required parameter for _create_domain_and_network

Closes-Bug: #1251261
(cherry picked from commit 81fc3967bca0f154d72d5de7875b646e1b6c47c8)

Conflicts:
	nova/tests/compute/test_compute_mgr.py
	nova/virt/vmwareapi/vmops.py

Change-Id: I72d131fc8dce903400e3080d51ba0fc0a1320751

TBH I'm not fully sold on the idea of associating an entity with an entity in order to measure to the performance of that entity, as we'd expect that to be broadly similar for all entities with same archiving policies.

e.g. if we're finding that the overhead of writing to some timeseries is way higher than for others, say on the basis of the number of datapoints already in the timeseries, then that would suggest a fairly fundamental problem in the storage driver implementation.

But in any case, the patch that introduced the circularity has already landed, so it doesn't make sense to hold up this current patch.

However should we consider re-organizing the model class hierarchy such that the Rosource->Entity relationship is encapsulated in say a separate Measurable mix-in, so we'd have:

       Resource
          ^
          |
      ----------
     |         |
  Entity   Measurable
                ^
                |
         --------------
        |              |
      Image       Instance ...

with:

  Measurable --[1:N]-- Entity

so that Measurable becomes the thing that has entities associated with it? (... and probably also stands in for our current concept of "generic resource")

In any case, let's land this patch now and then address that potential change to the model in a separate patch if necessary.

Cheers,
Eoghan'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-09-18 13:13:23.000000000', 'content': 'Change has been successfully merged into the git repository.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-09-18 13:13:23.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Verified+2

commit_message:
rest: store archive_policy and export entities as resources

This allow to (only) retrieve the entities as resources on their
/resource/entity endpoint. We disallow any manipulation (POST/PATCH) on
this endpoint as we don't want this endpoint to allow changes (yet?).

Change-Id: I1260ec4f78d383e5bea25ecdbf08e44266cf005f

commit_message:
Remove uses of unicode() builtin

Some uses of unicode() appear to have crept into glance's codebase. This
change replaces them with the recommended six.text_type().

Change-Id: I239f91114a921d3276da5cfd96ec1fde10601565
Partial-bug: #1282893

commit_message:
Fix Py3 compatibility issues

* Replace of urllib by six urlparse
* Convert dict keys into list to be able to retrieve the first element
* Use integer division for integers
* Use int instead of long in XML serialization/deserialization under Py3

Co-author: Cyril Roelandt <cyril.roelandt@enovance.com>

Change-Id: Ia79c831310775bf1c3dbec06010f8949c3a73887

commit_message:
Some tcp configuration paramters are ignored

The values for tcp_keepalive, tcp_keepidle, tcp_keepalive_count and
tcp_keepalive_interval in cinder.conf are not being picked up.

Change-Id: Ie0a232ae6b9b9a34d57b48f3b0d8694f90504517
Closes-bug: #1366011

Add description about central and compute agent HA

Add description about the HA support for central and compute agent
of Telemetry into the Admin Guide chapter. Also a typo is fixed.

commit_message:
Make user creation optional when creating service.

In some cases it is useful to be able to just configure
the service in Keystone and not the service user. This
is the case when e.g. a read only LDAP backend is used.
Added parameters configure_user and configure_user_role
(default to true).

Change-Id: I021976f1eafa881755c0abbe1f6ba1b546dee111
Closes-Bug: 1360232

commit_message:
Make user creation optional when creating service.

In some cases it is useful to be able to just configure
the service in Keystone and not the service user. This
is the case when e.g. a read only LDAP backend is used.
Added parameters configure_user and configure_user_role
(default to true).

Change-Id: If9bb802ff2bb0b3ece55f36df773059ba9c7e9de
Closes-Bug: 1360232

commit_message:
Raise correct exception in _execute_sql

Method _execute_sql() in oslo.db suppose, that we can get only
reason for the OperationalError - wrong DB admin credentials.
We should avoid of such suggestions, because it hides the original
error from database and make debugging more difficult. Handle
error message and raise DBConnectionError if we get connection
error, reraise original exception otherwise.

Closes-Bug: #1366850

Change-Id: I173dead4e522e00c82ec7aa1a12717e9ec903454
